<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Count
                                    <persName type="to">Cassini</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Your telegram of yesterday
                            reached me in the evening. As I explained to Mr. Hansen, the request of
                            my telegram of the 14th for a decision between the alternatives in the
                                <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi> case was superseded by the formal
                            application of Captain Berlinsky and by my telegram to you of yesterday
                            morning apprising you of the decision to disarm. I am glad the incident
                            has been so satisfactorily closed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>